aas_core.aas3_0.types.model

Interface IQualifier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IClass, IHasSemantics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnhancedQualifier, Qualifier

    public interface IQualifier
extends IHasSemantics
    A qualifier is a type-value-pair that makes additional statements w.r.t. the value of the element.

    Constraints:

    • Constraint AASd-006: If both the getValue() and the getValueId() of a Qualifier are present then the getValue() needs to be identical to the value of the referenced coded value in getValueId().
    • Constraint AASd-020: The value of getValue() shall be consistent to the data type as defined in getValueType().
